#. <section class="sutta" id="an8.19"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an8.19:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 8"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 8"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.19:0.2"
msgid "2. Mahāvagga"
msgstr "2. The Great Chapter"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an8.19:0.3"
msgid "19. Pahārādasutta"
msgstr "19. With Pahārāda"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an8.19:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā verañjāyaṃ viharati naḷerupucimandamūle."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying in Verañja at the root of a neem tree "
"dedicated to Naḷeru."

msgctxt "an8.19:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho pahārādo asurindo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhitaṃ kho pahārādaṃ "
"asurindaṃ bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Pahārāda the lord of demons went up to the Buddha, bowed, and stood to "
"one side. The Buddha said to him:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.198"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
#. VAR: Api → kiṃ (mr)
msgctxt "an8.19:2.1"
msgid "“Api pana, pahārāda, asurā mahāsamudde abhiramantī”ti?"
msgstr "“Well, Pahārāda, do the demons love the ocean?”"

msgctxt "an8.19:2.2"
msgid "“Abhiramanti, bhante, asurā mahāsamudde”ti."
msgstr "“Sir, they do indeed.”"

#. VAR: abbhutā dhammā → abbhutadhammā (s1-3, mr)
msgctxt "an8.19:2.3"
msgid ""
"“Kati pana, pahārāda, mahāsamudde acchariyā abbhutā dhammā, ye disvā disvā "
"asurā mahāsamudde abhiramantī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But seeing what incredible and amazing things do the demons love the ocean?”"

msgctxt "an8.19:2.4"
msgid ""
"“Aṭṭha, bhante, mahāsamudde acchariyā abbhutā dhammā, ye disvā disvā asurā "
"mahāsamudde abhiramanti."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, seeing eight incredible and amazing things the demons love the ocean."

msgctxt "an8.19:2.5"
msgid "Katame aṭṭha?"
msgstr "What eight?"

msgctxt "an8.19:2.6"
msgid ""
"Mahāsamuddo, bhante, anupubbaninno anupubbapoṇo anupubbapabbhāro, na "
"āyatakeneva papāto."
msgstr ""
"The ocean gradually slants, slopes, and inclines, with no abrupt precipice."

msgctxt "an8.19:2.7"
msgid ""
"Yampi, bhante, mahāsamuddo anupubbaninno anupubbapoṇo anupubbapabbhāro, na "
"āyatakeneva papāto;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an8.19:2.8"
msgid ""
"ayaṃ, bhante, mahāsamudde paṭhamo acchariyo abbhuto dhammo, yaṃ disvā disvā "
"asurā mahāsamudde abhiramanti. (1)"
msgstr "This is the first thing the demons love about the ocean."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an8.19:3.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhante, mahāsamuddo ṭhitadhammo velaṃ nātivattati."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, the ocean is consistent and doesn’t overflow its boundaries."

msgctxt "an8.19:3.2"
msgid "Yampi, bhante, mahāsamuddo ṭhitadhammo velaṃ nātivattati;"
msgstr ""

#. VAR: ayaṃ → ayampi (mr)
msgctxt "an8.19:3.3"
msgid ""
"ayaṃ, bhante, mahāsamudde dutiyo acchariyo abbhuto dhammo yaṃ disvā disvā "
"asurā mahāsamudde abhiramanti. (2)"
msgstr "This is the second thing the demons love about the ocean."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
#. VAR: saṃvasati → saṃvattati (s1-3)
msgctxt "an8.19:4.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhante, mahāsamuddo na matena kuṇapena saṃvasati."
msgstr "Furthermore, the ocean doesn’t accommodate a corpse,"

msgctxt "an8.19:4.2"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ hoti mahāsamudde mataṃ kuṇapaṃ, taṃ khippameva tīraṃ vāheti, thalaṃ "
"ussāreti."
msgstr "but quickly carries it to the shore and strands it on the beach."

msgctxt "an8.19:4.3"
msgid ""
"Yampi, bhante, mahāsamuddo na matena kuṇapena saṃvasati, yaṃ hoti "
"mahāsamudde mataṃ kuṇapaṃ, taṃ khippameva tīraṃ vāheti, thalaṃ ussāreti;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an8.19:4.4"
msgid ""
"ayaṃ, bhante, mahāsamudde tatiyo acchariyo abbhuto dhammo, yaṃ disvā disvā "
"asurā mahāsamudde abhiramanti. (3)"
msgstr "This is the third thing the demons love about the ocean."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.199"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an8.19:5.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhante, yā kāci mahānadiyo, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "Furthermore, when they reach the ocean, all the great rivers—that is,"

# BB has designation"for gotta, but I think the point here is that the text is, in fact, a little incongruous. In the Upanishadic passage this is presumably derived from, it has “namarupa”, which makes better sense.
msgctxt "an8.19:5.2"
msgid ""
"gaṅgā yamunā aciravatī sarabhū mahī, tā mahāsamuddaṃ patvā jahanti purimāni "
"nāmagottāni, ‘mahāsamuddo’ tveva saṅkhaṃ gacchanti."
msgstr ""
"the Ganges, Yamunā, Aciravatī, Sarabhū, and Mahī—lose their names and clans "
"and are simply considered ‘the ocean’."

msgctxt "an8.19:5.3"
msgid ""
"Yampi, bhante, yā kāci mahānadiyo, seyyathidaṃ—gaṅgā yamunā aciravatī "
"sarabhū mahī, tā mahāsamuddaṃ patvā jahanti purimāni nāmagottāni, "
"‘mahāsamuddo’ tveva saṅkhaṃ gacchanti;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an8.19:5.4"
msgid ""
"ayaṃ, bhante, mahāsamudde catuttho acchariyo abbhuto dhammo, yaṃ disvā disvā "
"asurā mahāsamudde abhiramanti. (4)"
msgstr "This is the fourth thing the demons love about the ocean."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
#. VAR: bhante, yā ca → yā kāci (s1-3, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an8.19:6.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhante, yā ca loke savantiyo mahāsamuddaṃ appenti yā ca "
"antalikkhā dhārā papatanti, na tena mahāsamuddassa ūnattaṃ vā pūrattaṃ vā "
"paññāyati."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, for all the world’s streams that reach it, and the rain that "
"falls from the sky, the ocean never empties or fills up."

msgctxt "an8.19:6.2"
msgid ""
"Yampi, bhante, yā ca loke savantiyo mahāsamuddaṃ appenti yā ca antalikkhā "
"dhārā papatanti, na tena mahāsamuddassa ūnattaṃ vā pūrattaṃ vā paññāyati;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an8.19:6.3"
msgid ""
"ayaṃ, bhante, mahāsamudde pañcamo acchariyo abbhuto dhammo, yaṃ disvā disvā "
"asurā mahāsamudde abhiramanti. (5)"
msgstr "This is the fifth thing the demons love about the ocean."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an8.19:7.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhante, mahāsamuddo ekaraso loṇaraso."
msgstr "Furthermore, the ocean has just one taste, the taste of salt."

msgctxt "an8.19:7.2"
msgid "Yampi, bhante, mahāsamuddo ekaraso loṇaraso;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an8.19:7.3"
msgid ""
"ayaṃ, bhante, mahāsamudde chaṭṭho acchariyo abbhuto dhammo, yaṃ disvā disvā "
"asurā mahāsamudde abhiramanti. (6)"
msgstr "This is the sixth thing the demons love about the ocean."

# Here and in some other places, BB has lapus lazuli for veluriya. This seems unlikely, however. LL is defined by a strong blue color and dull luster, which are not characteristics of veluriya. Rather veluriya is typically described as transparent, gleaming, and shiny, which sounds like beryl.
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.200"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
#. VAR: bahuratano → pahūtaratano (mr)
msgctxt "an8.19:8.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhante, mahāsamuddo bahuratano anekaratano. Tatrimāni "
"ratanāni, seyyathidaṃ—muttā maṇi veḷuriyo saṅkho silā pavāḷaṃ rajataṃ "
"jātarūpaṃ lohitako masāragallaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, the ocean is full of many kinds of treasures, such as pearls, "
"gems, beryl, conch, quartz, coral, silver, gold, rubies, and emeralds."

msgctxt "an8.19:8.2"
msgid ""
"Yampi, bhante, mahāsamuddo bahuratano anekaratano; tatrimāni ratanāni, "
"seyyathidaṃ—muttā maṇi veḷuriyo saṅkho silā pavāḷaṃ rajataṃ jātarūpaṃ "
"lohitako masāragallaṃ;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an8.19:8.3"
msgid ""
"ayaṃ, bhante, mahāsamudde sattamo acchariyo abbhuto dhammo, yaṃ disvā disvā "
"asurā mahāsamudde abhiramanti. (7)"
msgstr "This is the seventh thing the demons love about the ocean."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
#. VAR: timi timiṅgalā timirapiṅgalā (bj) | timitimiṅgalā timiramiṅgalā (s1-3, pts1) | timi timiṅgalo timitimiṅgalo ()
msgctxt "an8.19:9.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhante, mahāsamuddo mahataṃ bhūtānaṃ āvāso. Tatrime bhūtā—timi "
"timiṅgalo timirapiṅgalo asurā nāgā gandhabbā. Santi mahāsamudde "
"yojanasatikāpi attabhāvā, dviyojanasatikāpi attabhāvā, tiyojanasatikāpi "
"attabhāvā, catuyojanasatikāpi attabhāvā, pañcayojanasatikāpi attabhāvā."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, many great beings live in the ocean, such as leviathans, "
"leviathan-gulpers, leviathan-gulper-gulpers, demons, dragons, and fairies. "
"In the ocean there are life-forms a hundred leagues long, or even two "
"hundred, three hundred, four hundred, or five hundred leagues long."

msgctxt "an8.19:9.2"
msgid ""
"Yampi, bhante, mahāsamuddo mahataṃ bhūtānaṃ āvāso; tatrime bhūtā—timi "
"timiṅgalo timirapiṅgalo asurā nāgā gandhabbā; santi mahāsamudde "
"yojanasatikāpi attabhāvā … pe … tiyojana … catuyojana … pañcayojanasatikāpi "
"attabhāvā;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an8.19:9.3"
msgid ""
"ayaṃ, bhante, mahāsamudde aṭṭhamo acchariyo abbhuto dhammo, yaṃ disvā disvā "
"asurā mahāsamudde abhiramanti."
msgstr "This is the eighth thing the demons love about the ocean."

msgctxt "an8.19:9.4"
msgid ""
"Ime kho, bhante, mahāsamudde aṭṭha acchariyā abbhutā dhammā, ye disvā disvā "
"asurā mahāsamudde abhiramantīti. (8)"
msgstr ""
"Seeing these eight incredible and amazing things the demons love the ocean."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.201"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "an8.19:10.1"
msgid "Api pana, bhante, bhikkhū imasmiṃ dhammavinaye abhiramantī”ti?"
msgstr "Well, sir, do the mendicants love this teaching and training?”"

msgctxt "an8.19:10.2"
msgid "“Abhiramanti, pahārāda, bhikkhū imasmiṃ dhammavinaye”ti."
msgstr "“They do indeed, Pahārāda.”"

msgctxt "an8.19:10.3"
msgid ""
"“Kati pana, bhante, imasmiṃ dhammavinaye acchariyā abbhutā dhammā, ye disvā "
"disvā bhikkhū imasmiṃ dhammavinaye abhiramantī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But seeing how many incredible and amazing things do the mendicants love "
"this teaching and training?”"

msgctxt "an8.19:10.4"
msgid ""
"“Aṭṭha, pahārāda, imasmiṃ dhammavinaye acchariyā abbhutā dhammā, ye disvā "
"disvā bhikkhū imasmiṃ dhammavinaye abhiramanti."
msgstr ""
"“Seeing eight incredible and amazing things, Pahārāda, the mendicants love "
"this teaching and training."

msgctxt "an8.19:10.5"
msgid "Katame aṭṭha?"
msgstr "What eight?"

msgctxt "an8.19:10.6"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, pahārāda, mahāsamuddo anupubbaninno anupubbapoṇo "
"anupubbapabbhāro, na āyatakeneva papāto;"
msgstr ""
"The ocean gradually slants, slopes, and inclines, with no abrupt precipice."

msgctxt "an8.19:10.7"
msgid ""
"evamevaṃ kho, pahārāda, imasmiṃ dhammavinaye anupubbasikkhā anupubbakiriyā "
"anupubbapaṭipadā, na āyatakeneva aññāpaṭivedho."
msgstr ""
"In the same way in this teaching and training the penetration to "
"enlightenment comes from gradual training, progress, and practice, not "
"abruptly."

msgctxt "an8.19:10.8"
msgid ""
"Yampi, pahārāda, imasmiṃ dhammavinaye anupubbasikkhā anupubbakiriyā "
"anupubbapaṭipadā, na āyatakeneva aññāpaṭivedho;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an8.19:10.9"
msgid ""
"ayaṃ, pahārāda, imasmiṃ dhammavinaye paṭhamo acchariyo abbhuto dhammo, yaṃ "
"disvā disvā bhikkhū imasmiṃ dhammavinaye abhiramanti. (1)"
msgstr ""
"This is the first thing the mendicants love about this teaching and training."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "an8.19:11.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, pahārāda, mahāsamuddo ṭhitadhammo velaṃ nātivattati;"
msgstr "The ocean is consistent and doesn’t overflow its boundaries."

msgctxt "an8.19:11.2"
msgid ""
"evamevaṃ kho, pahārāda, yaṃ mayā sāvakānaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ taṃ mama "
"sāvakā jīvitahetupi nātikkamanti."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, when a training rule is laid down for my disciples they "
"wouldn’t break it even for the sake of their own life."

msgctxt "an8.19:11.3"
msgid ""
"Yampi, pahārāda, mayā sāvakānaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ taṃ mama sāvakā "
"jīvitahetupi nātikkamanti;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an8.19:11.4"
msgid ""
"ayaṃ, pahārāda, imasmiṃ dhammavinaye dutiyo acchariyo abbhuto dhammo, yaṃ "
"disvā disvā bhikkhū imasmiṃ dhammavinaye abhiramanti. (2)"
msgstr ""
"This is the second thing the mendicants love about this teaching and "
"training."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "an8.19:12.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, pahārāda, mahāsamuddo na matena kuṇapena saṃvasati. Yaṃ hoti "
"mahāsamudde mataṃ kuṇapaṃ, taṃ khippameva tīraṃ vāheti thalaṃ ussāreti;"
msgstr ""
"The ocean doesn’t accommodate a corpse, but quickly carries it to the shore "
"and strands it on the beach."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.202"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "an8.19:13.1"
msgid ""
"evamevaṃ kho, pahārāda, yo so puggalo dussīlo pāpadhammo "
"asucisaṅkassarasamācāro paṭicchannakammanto assamaṇo samaṇapaṭiñño "
"abrahmacārī brahmacāripaṭiñño antopūti avassuto kasambujāto, na tena saṅgho "
"saṃvasati; khippameva naṃ sannipatitvā ukkhipati. Kiñcāpi so hoti majjhe "
"bhikkhusaṅghassa sannisinno, atha kho so ārakāva saṅghamhā saṅgho ca tena."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, the Saṅgha doesn’t accommodate a person who is unethical, "
"of bad qualities, filthy, with suspicious behavior, underhand, no true "
"ascetic or spiritual practitioner—though claiming to be one—rotten inside, "
"corrupt, and depraved. But they quickly gather and expel them. Even if such "
"a person is sitting in the middle of the Saṅgha, they’re far from the "
"Saṅgha, and the Saṅgha is far from them."

msgctxt "an8.19:13.2"
msgid ""
"Yampi, pahārāda, yo so puggalo dussīlo pāpadhammo asucisaṅkassarasamācāro "
"paṭicchannakammanto assamaṇo samaṇapaṭiñño abrahmacārī brahmacāripaṭiñño "
"antopūti avassuto kasambujāto, na tena saṅgho saṃvasati; khippameva naṃ "
"sannipatitvā ukkhipati; kiñcāpi so hoti majjhe bhikkhusaṅghassa sannisinno, "
"atha kho so ārakāva saṅghamhā saṅgho ca tena;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an8.19:13.3"
msgid ""
"ayaṃ, pahārāda, imasmiṃ dhammavinaye tatiyo acchariyo abbhuto dhammo, yaṃ "
"disvā disvā bhikkhū imasmiṃ dhammavinaye abhiramanti. (3)"
msgstr ""
"This is the third thing the mendicants love about this teaching and training."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "an8.19:14.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, pahārāda, yā kāci mahānadiyo, seyyathidaṃ—gaṅgā yamunā aciravatī "
"sarabhū mahī, tā mahāsamuddaṃ patvā jahanti purimāni nāmagottāni, "
"‘mahāsamuddo’ tveva saṅkhaṃ gacchanti;"
msgstr ""
"When they reach the ocean, all the great rivers—that is, the Ganges, Yamunā, "
"Aciravatī, Sarabhū, and Mahī—lose their names and clans and are simply "
"considered ‘the ocean’."

#. VAR: samaṇā sakyaputtiyā’ tveva → samaṇo sakyaputtiyotveva (s1-3, mr)
msgctxt "an8.19:14.2"
msgid ""
"evamevaṃ kho, pahārāda, cattārome vaṇṇā—khattiyā, brāhmaṇā, vessā, suddā, te "
"tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitvā jahanti "
"purimāni nāmagottāni, ‘samaṇā sakyaputtiyā’ tveva saṅkhaṃ gacchanti."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, when they go forth from the lay life to homelessness, all "
"four castes—aristocrats, brahmins, merchants, and workers—lose their former "
"names and clans and are simply considered ‘Sakyan ascetics’."

msgctxt "an8.19:14.3"
msgid ""
"Yampi, pahārāda, cattārome vaṇṇā—khattiyā, brāhmaṇā, vessā, suddā, te "
"tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitvā jahanti "
"purimāni nāmagottāni, ‘samaṇā sakyaputtiyā’ tveva saṅkhaṃ gacchanti;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an8.19:14.4"
msgid ""
"ayaṃ, pahārāda, imasmiṃ dhammavinaye catuttho acchariyo abbhuto dhammo, yaṃ "
"disvā disvā bhikkhū imasmiṃ dhammavinaye abhiramanti. (4)"
msgstr ""
"This is the fourth thing the mendicants love about this teaching and "
"training."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.203"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "an8.19:15.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, pahārāda, yā ca loke savantiyo mahāsamuddaṃ appenti yā ca "
"antalikkhā dhārā papatanti, na tena mahāsamuddassa ūnattaṃ vā pūrattaṃ vā "
"paññāyati;"
msgstr ""
"For all the world’s streams that reach it, and the rain that falls from the "
"sky, the ocean never empties or fills up."

msgctxt "an8.19:15.2"
msgid ""
"evamevaṃ kho, pahārāda, bahū cepi bhikkhū anupādisesāya nibbānadhātuyā "
"parinibbāyanti, na tena nibbānadhātuyā ūnattaṃ vā pūrattaṃ vā paññāyati."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, though several mendicants become fully extinguished through "
"the natural principle of extinguishment, without anything left over, the "
"natural principle of extinguishment never empties or fills up."

msgctxt "an8.19:15.3"
msgid ""
"Yampi, pahārāda, bahū cepi bhikkhū anupādisesāya nibbānadhātuyā "
"parinibbāyanti, na tena nibbānadhātuyā ūnattaṃ vā pūrattaṃ vā paññāyati;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an8.19:15.4"
msgid ""
"ayaṃ, pahārāda, imasmiṃ dhammavinaye pañcamo acchariyo abbhuto dhammo, yaṃ "
"disvā disvā bhikkhū imasmiṃ dhammavinaye abhiramanti. (5)"
msgstr ""
"This is the fifth thing the mendicants love about this teaching and training."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "an8.19:16.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, pahārāda, mahāsamuddo ekaraso loṇaraso;"
msgstr "The ocean has just one taste, the taste of salt."

msgctxt "an8.19:16.2"
msgid "evamevaṃ kho, pahārāda, ayaṃ dhammavinayo ekaraso, vimuttiraso."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, this teaching and training has one taste, the taste of "
"freedom."

msgctxt "an8.19:16.3"
msgid "Yampi, pahārāda, ayaṃ dhammavinayo ekaraso, vimuttiraso;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an8.19:16.4"
msgid ""
"ayaṃ, pahārāda, imasmiṃ dhammavinaye chaṭṭho acchariyo abbhuto dhammo, yaṃ "
"disvā disvā bhikkhū imasmiṃ dhammavinaye abhiramanti. (6)"
msgstr ""
"This is the sixth thing the mendicants love about this teaching and training."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc17"></a>
msgctxt "an8.19:17.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, pahārāda, mahāsamuddo bahuratano anekaratano; tatrimāni "
"ratanāni, seyyathidaṃ—muttā maṇi veḷuriyo saṅkho silā pavāḷaṃ rajataṃ "
"jātarūpaṃ lohitako masāragallaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"The ocean is full of many kinds of treasures, such as pearls, gems, beryl, "
"conch, quartz, coral, silver, gold, rubies, and emeralds."

msgctxt "an8.19:17.2"
msgid ""
"evamevaṃ kho, pahārāda, ayaṃ dhammavinayo bahuratano anekaratano. Tatrimāni "
"ratanāni, seyyathidaṃ—cattāro satipaṭṭhānā, cattāro sammappadhānā, cattāro "
"iddhipādā, pañcindriyāni, pañca balāni, satta bojjhaṅgā, ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko "
"maggo."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, this teaching and training is full of many kinds of "
"treasures, such as the four kinds of mindfulness meditation, the four right "
"efforts, the four bases for psychic power, the five faculties, the five "
"powers, the seven awakening factors, and the noble eightfold path."

msgctxt "an8.19:17.3"
msgid ""
"Yampi, pahārāda, ayaṃ dhammavinayo bahuratano anekaratano; tatrimāni "
"ratanāni, seyyathidaṃ—cattāro satipaṭṭhānā, cattāro sammappadhānā, cattāro "
"iddhipādā, pañcindriyāni, pañca balāni, satta bojjhaṅgā, ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko "
"maggo;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an8.19:17.4"
msgid ""
"ayaṃ, pahārāda, imasmiṃ dhammavinaye sattamo acchariyo abbhuto dhammo, yaṃ "
"disvā disvā bhikkhū imasmiṃ dhammavinaye abhiramanti. (7)"
msgstr ""
"This is the seventh thing the mendicants love about this teaching and "
"training."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.204"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc18"></a>
msgctxt "an8.19:18.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, pahārāda, mahāsamuddo mahataṃ bhūtānaṃ āvāso; tatrime bhūtā—timi "
"timiṅgalo timirapiṅgalo asurā nāgā gandhabbā; santi mahāsamudde "
"yojanasatikāpi attabhāvā, dviyojanasatikāpi attabhāvā, tiyojanasatikāpi "
"attabhāvā, catuyojanasatikāpi attabhāvā, pañcayojanasatikāpi attabhāvā;"
msgstr ""
"Many great beings live in the ocean, such as leviathans, leviathan-gulpers, "
"leviathan-gulper-gulpers, demons, dragons, and fairies. In the ocean there "
"are life-forms a hundred leagues long, or even two hundred, three hundred, "
"four hundred, or five hundred leagues long."

msgctxt "an8.19:18.2"
msgid ""
"evamevaṃ kho, pahārāda, ayaṃ dhammavinayo mahataṃ bhūtānaṃ āvāso; tatrime "
"bhūtā—sotāpanno sotāpattiphalasacchikiriyāya paṭipanno, sakadāgāmī "
"sakadāgāmiphalasacchikiriyāya paṭipanno, anāgāmī anāgāmiphalasacchikiriyāya "
"paṭipanno, arahā arahattāya paṭipanno."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, great beings live in this teaching and training, and these "
"are those beings. The stream-enterer and the one practicing to realize the "
"fruit of stream-entry. The once-returner and the one practicing to realize "
"the fruit of once-return. The non-returner and the one practicing to realize "
"the fruit of non-return. The perfected ones, and the one practicing for "
"perfection."

msgctxt "an8.19:18.3"
msgid ""
"Yampi, pahārāda, ayaṃ dhammavinayo mahataṃ bhūtānaṃ āvāso; tatrime bhūtā—"
"sotāpanno sotāpattiphalasacchikiriyāya paṭipanno, sakadāgāmī "
"sakadāgāmiphalasacchikiriyāya paṭipanno, anāgāmī anāgāmiphalasacchikiriyāya "
"paṭipanno, arahā arahattāya paṭipanno;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an8.19:18.4"
msgid ""
"ayaṃ, pahārāda, imasmiṃ dhammavinaye aṭṭhamo acchariyo abbhuto dhammo, yaṃ "
"disvā disvā bhikkhū imasmiṃ dhammavinaye abhiramanti. (8)"
msgstr ""
"This is the eighth thing the mendicants love about this teaching and "
"training."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc19"></a>
msgctxt "an8.19:19.1"
msgid ""
"Ime kho, pahārāda, imasmiṃ dhammavinaye aṭṭha acchariyā abbhutā dhammā, ye "
"disvā disvā bhikkhū imasmiṃ dhammavinaye abhiramantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"Seeing these eight incredible and amazing things, Pahārāda, the mendicants "
"love this teaching and training.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an8.19:19.2"
msgid "Navamaṃ."
msgstr ""
